	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>You burn incense and cast layered interwoven blessings or curses to ward the area against unwanted magical creatures, who are damaged as they approach.</em></p><p><strong>Optional Materials:</strong> If you use 1 lb of @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.cdHZSCT73fIbD3le]{Hallowed Incense}, typically valued at 500 gold, while casting this spell, this spell is permanent. This consumes the incense.</p><p><strong>Utility Spell</strong></p><ul><li><p>You touch a point and infuse an area around it with holy or unholy power. The area must fit inside a 60 ft. radius sphere and not overlap with another Hallow effect.</p></li><li><p>Choose one or more of these creature types: &amp;reference[Aberration], &amp;reference[Celestial], &amp;reference[Elemental], &amp;reference[Fey], &amp;reference[Fiend], and &amp;reference[Undead]. You can set specific creatures to be unaffected by the spell, and you can later allow a creature to enter unaffected. All others of the chosen type(s) are affected.</p></li><li><p>Affected creatures:</p><ul><li><p><span style=\"font-family:'Roboto Condensed', sans-serif\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;scrollbar-width:thin;scrollbar-color:rgb(93, 20, 43) rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\">Area Hazard: </strong>Affected creatures take </span>[[/damage 4d6 radiant ]] damage<span style=\"font-family:'Roboto Condensed', sans-serif\"> when they enter or when they end their turn in the area (but only once per turn).</span></p></li><li style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;scrollbar-width:thin;scrollbar-color:rgb(93, 20, 43) rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\"><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;scrollbar-width:thin;scrollbar-color:rgb(93, 20, 43) rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);margin:0.5em 0px\">Cannot &amp;reference[charmed]{charm}, &amp;reference[frightened]{frighten}, or &amp;reference[goaded]{goad}, or possess creatures in the area. If the affected creature charms, frightens, goads, or possesses a creature and that creature enters the Hallowed area, then the condition is suppressed until the creature leaves the Hallowed area.</p></li><li style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;scrollbar-width:thin;scrollbar-color:rgb(93, 20, 43) rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\"><p>Cannot be summoned, raised from the dead, or otherwise created in the area.</p></li><li><p>Can sense the hallowed area is dangerous to them once within 30 ft. of the Hallowed area's boundaries.</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Hallow is a &amp;reference[cursed]{curse} and cannot be dispelled, but it can be ended with <em>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.piOfkIqVwkpV4Znb]{Break Enchantment}</em>. A creature immune to curses is immune to Hallow's effects.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Upcasting:</strong> Increase damage by [[/damage 2d6 radiant]]{2d6} for each spell level above 5th.</p>",
			"chat": ""
		},
